The errata is probably to avoid situations where the Escaped Shapeshifters gain abilities and never lose them. Say we both have an ES, I cast [autocard]Leap[/autocard] on one of my creatures, your ES gains flying (at least until my creature loses it at end of turn), then my ES has flying because your ES has flying. At the end of the turn, Leap wears off, but my ES doesn't lose flying until your ES does, and your ES doesn't because I still have a flying ES. I'd have to look back at the rules when this came out (if I can find them), but the rules on temporary effects and how they wear off may have been subtly different back then, so the errata [i]may[/i] restore original design intent. 

